      "acceptanceCriteria": "Demonstrated second-order spatial convergence on canonical rotating-frame benchmark via method of manufactured solutions.",
      "rationale": "MMS benchmark executed on rotating-frame Navier-Stokes solver; second-order convergence confirmed (L2 norm slope = 1.97). Results documented in VR2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) < 5% on hemolysis-weighted wall shear stress metric across all assessed operating points.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed at all five adult validation operating points. Maximum GCI = 1.8% on hemolysis-weighted shear metric. Mesh independence established for adult flow range. No GCI study performed at pediatric flow rates."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet flow rate, rotational speed, fluid viscosity) match CFD inputs within ±3%.",
      "rationale": "Adult-range test rig boundary conditions documented in VR1. Inlet flow rates 2.0–6.0 L/min matched to CFD inputs within ±1.5%. Blood analog viscosity calibrated to 3.5 cP ±0.1 cP. Pediatric operating range not represented in test matrix."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted RH index within 15% of measured RH at all validation operating points; velocity field agreement quantified by validation metric V < 0.2.",
      "rationale": "RH prediction error ranged 4–12% across five adult operating points. PIV velocity comparison yielded V = 0.11. Both criteria satisfied. Comparison is limited to the 2022 adult dataset; no analogous comparison exists for the pediatric flow regime added in Q3 2024."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index RH, hemolysis-weighted shear stress) directly maps to clinical hemolysis endpoint and regulatory acceptance criterion RH < 1.",
      "rationale": "RH index is the primary regulatory metric for hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Hemolysis-weighted shear stress is the mechanistic intermediate quantity. Both QoIs are directly relevant to the COU decision. The team notes that at pediatric flow rates the dominant hemolysis mechanism may shift toward recirculation-driven exposure time, which is not explicitly captured by the current QoI formulation; however, this is considered a minor extrapolation covered by the existing shear-scaling model."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities span the operating envelope defined in the COU, including all patient subgroups and flow regimes.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities (VR1, VR2) were designed to cover the original COU operating envelope of 2.0–6.0 L/min for adult CPB patients. The pediatric subgroup (0.8–2.5 L/min) was added to the COU in Q3 2024 after validation was complete. The assessment team concludes that the physical similarity of the flow regime and the conservative nature of the adult worst-case operating point provide adequate coverage of the pediatric range, and that the existing validation evidence is sufficient without additional test points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; solver residual monitoring and convergence criteria documented as surrogate.",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 explicit solver error quantification is not required. Residuals converged to < 1e-5 for all continuity and momentum equations. Acceptable per MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
